{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"71e3879fe4a99614aee0344168f913a627a635efba176e2b65b7ad11aca3c6c8","slug":"papers.extra.index","location":"/papers/extra/index.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Extra & Emerging","description":"Ferroelectric synapses, organic neuromorphic devices, hybrid SNN architectures, AER systems, and frontier topics.","content_includes_title":false,"exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"index.md","url":"/index-41e3db347ef85b67c5313ae02c76f765.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What is this domain?","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"key":"B8R1mMHktV"}],"identifier":"what-is-this-domain","label":"What is this domain?","html_id":"what-is-this-domain","implicit":true,"key":"rbLcijLgdz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This section collects recent and edge papers that do not fit cleanly within any single thematic section, or that span multiple sections in novel ways. Topics include emerging device technologies such as ferroelectric tunnel junctions and organic electrochemical transistors, hybrid architectures that combine spiking neural networks with conventional deep learning pipelines, advanced AER communication systems, and speculative but scientifically grounded proposals for the next generation of neuromorphic computing.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"qAdT4JlQLI"}],"key":"eYEdzzAEKP"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why it matters","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"key":"HHU2IySODS"}],"identifier":"why-it-matters","label":"Why it matters","html_id":"why-it-matters","implicit":true,"key":"qvNqdTG9sE"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The frontier of neuromorphic research often appears here first, before it consolidates into a distinct subfield. Ferroelectric synapses and organic devices may offer advantages in scalability, flexibility, or biocompatibility that oxide-based RRAM cannot match. Hybrid SNN-ANN architectures acknowledge that spiking and rate-coded computation may each be optimal for different tasks, and that real systems will blend both. Tracking these developments prevents the knowledge base from calcifying around established paradigms.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"key":"z6yz6TiphJ"}],"key":"beXGKGQQFq"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Core concepts","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"SSM4Fo35HC"}],"identifier":"core-concepts","label":"Core concepts","html_id":"core-concepts","implicit":true,"key":"DmLKoCfRMT"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ferroelectric synaptic devices","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"LfMNDl2Esy"}],"key":"IDECmlQLpc"},{"type":"text","value":" — ferroelectric tunnel junctions (FTJs) and ferroelectric field-effect transistors (FeFETs) use polarisation switching in perovskite films (e.g. HfO₂:Si, BaTiO₃) to implement analogue synaptic weights with nanosecond switching and CMOS compatibility","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"IDMLaC2HD6"}],"key":"KrGzzvOTFE"}],"key":"uV18SNP7DM"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Organic neuromorphic devices","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"Ope7O6ZXvT"}],"key":"CZBwDabDMJ"},{"type":"text","value":" — electrochemical transistors based on conducting polymers (e.g. PEDOT:PSS) exhibit ion-mediated conductance modulation that closely mimics short- and long-term synaptic plasticity; inherently soft and biocompatible","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"M05ACnmgxS"}],"key":"UAZNN31dd1"}],"key":"jPQvtk3Bcl"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hybrid SNN-ANN architectures","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"SyVnWHxnhj"}],"key":"BCA0580a5V"},{"type":"text","value":" — systems that use spiking layers for event-driven preprocessing or temporal processing and rate-coded layers for classification or regression, combining the energy efficiency of SNNs with the training maturity of ANNs","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":1},"end":{"line":20,"column":1}},"key":"bjUIii79cx"}],"key":"KAnXHTOod6"}],"key":"stzqB0cnjY"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"chi